lper template definition** <br> `charts/social-media-reuploader/templates/_helpers.tpl`|New `social-media-reuploader.labels` helper defines standard Kubernetes labels using app name, instance, version, and chart metadata; outputs labels as YAML for reuse across resources.|\n|**Deployment labels and BOT_TOKEN handling** <br> `charts/social-media-reuploader/templates/deployment.yaml`|Deployment metadata.labels, pod-template labels, and selector use the centralized label helper; `BOT_TOKEN` env var supports Secret, inline env, or emits a template comment when absent.|\n|**GUI Deployment & Service and core Services** <br> `charts/social-media-reuploader/templates/gui-deployment.yaml`, `charts/social-media-reuploader/templates/gui-service.yaml`, `charts/social-media-reuploader/templates/service.yaml`|GUI Deployment/Service and core Service add standard metadata.labels and migrate selectors to `app.kubernetes.io/instance` with component keys for consistent pod matching.|\n|**Secondary resources and Secret validation** <br> `charts/.../db-pvc.yaml`, `charts/.../serviceaccount.yaml`, `charts/.../ingress.yaml`, `charts/.../httproute.yaml`, `charts/.../secret.yaml`|PVC, ServiceAccount, Ingress, HTTPRoute, and Secret templates add metadata.labels from the helper; Secret creation is conditional and fails rendering if BOT_TOKEN is empty.|\n|**Values defaults and env docs** <br> `charts/social-media-reuploader/values.yaml`|Adds `nameOverride`/`fullnameOverride`, `imagePullSecrets`, and updates env documentation: removes default BOT_TOKEN, sets webhook defaults, and documents recommended Secret usage.|\n\n**Media Processing Enhancement**\n\n|Layer / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Media inspection and codec detection** <br> `src/downloader.py`|Imports `json` and runs `ffprobe` (when available) to parse stream/format metadata and detect presence of video/audio and codec names.|\n|**Video+audio transcode or remux** <br> `src/downloader.py`|When both video and audio streams are present, selects between transcoding to H.264/AAC or remuxing to MP4 with `+faststart` based on codec/container compatibility; updates output on success.|\n|**Audio-only wrapping and fallback recode** <br> `src/downloader.py`|For audio-only outputs, attempts an ffmpeg wrapper (black video + AAC) when available, otherwise falls back to `yt-dlp --recode-video mp4`; updates latest/extension on success and includes a secondary wrapper path.|\n\n**Application Reliability and CI/CD Hardening**\n\n|Layer / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Container health endpoint monitoring** <br> `Dockerfile`|Adds `HEALTHCHECK` instruction probing `/health` on port 8080 and expecting HTTP 200 for liveness.|\n|**Docker release workflow authorization** <br> `.github/workflows/docker-release.yml`|Introduces `DOCKER_RELEASE_ALLOWED_AUTHOR` and gates the `build` job with an `if:` that restricts runs to the repo owner, the allowed override, or GitHub Actions bot authors; adds a debug step logging the resolved author and actor.|\n|**Deployment workflow optimization & docs** <br> `.github/workflows/docs-deploy.yml`, `.github/workflows/release-please.yml`|Docs deploy now triggers only for `docs/**`, `mkdocs.yml`, or `README.md` changes; release-please workflow trigger changed to pushes on `main` and adds a note about disabling auto-publishing; CONTRIBUTING.md documents how to fix Conventional Commit messages locally.|\n\n## Estimated code review effort\n\n🎯 4 (Complex) | ⏱️ ~45 minutes\n\n## Poem\n\n> 🐰 I hopped through charts and labels tonight,  \n> > ffprobe whispered codecs, dim and bright,  \n> > I wrapped sad audio in tiny MP4 beds,  \n> > Healthcheck taps gently where /health path treads,  \n> > Release gates blink — the burrow nods and rests.\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 4 | ❌ 1</summary>\n\n### ❌ Failed checks (1 inconclusive)\n\n|  Check name | Status         | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                                 | Resolution                                                                                                                                                    |\n| :---------: | :------------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n| Title check | ❓ Inconclusive | The title is too vague and generic. It uses non-descriptive terms 'Fix deployment and file format' that don't convey meaningful information about the substantial changes in the changeset. | Provide a more specific title that captures the main changes, such as 'Add Kubernetes labels to Helm templates and improve Docker/media handling' or similar. |\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (4 passed)</summary>\n\n|         Check name         | Status   | Explanation                                                                          |\n| :------------------------: | :------- | :----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|      Description Check     | ✅ Passed | Check skipped - CodeRabbit’s high-level summary is enabled.                          |\n|     Docstring Coverage     | ✅ Passed | Docstring coverage is 100.00% which is sufficient. The required threshold is 80.00%. |\n|     Linked Issues check    | ✅ Passed | Check skipped because no linked issues were found for this pull request.             |\n| Out of Scope Changes check | ✅ Passed | Check skipped because no linked issues were found for this pull request.             |\n\n</details>\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can configure your own custom pre-merge checks in the settings.</sub>\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_end -->\n<!-- finishing_touch_checkbox_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>✨ Finishing Touches</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Generate docstrings</summary>\n\n- [ ] <!-- {\"checkboxId\": \"7962f53c-55bc-4827-bfbf-6a18da830691\"} --> Create stacked PR\n- [ ] <!-- {\"checkboxId\": \"3e1879ae-f29b-4d0d-8e06-d12b7ba33d98\"} --> Commit on current branch\n\n</details>\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- finishing_touch_checkbox_end -->\n<!-- tips_start -->\n\n---\n\nThanks for using [CodeRabbit](https://coderabbit.ai?utm_source=oss&utm_medium=github&utm_campaign=lucaam/social-media-reuploader&utm_content=5)! It's free for OSS, and your support helps us grow. If you like it, consider giving us a shout-out.\n\n<details>\n<summary>❤️ Share</summary>\n\n- [X](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=I%20just%20used%20%40coderabbitai%20for%20my%20code%20review%2C%20and%20it%27s%20fantastic%21%20It%27s%20free%20for%20OSS%20and%20offers%20a%20free%20trial%20for%20the%20proprietary%20code.%20Check%20it%20out%3A&url=https%3A//coderabbit.ai)\n- [Mastodon](https://mastodon.social/share?text=I%20just%20used%20%40coderabbitai%20for%20my%20code%20review%2C%20and%20it%27s%20fantastic%21%20It%27s%20free%20for%20OSS%20and%20offers%20a%20free%20trial%20for%20the%20proprietary%20code.%20Check%20it%20out%3A%20https%3A%2F%2Fcoderabbit.ai)\n- [Reddit](https://www.reddit.com/submit?title=Great%20tool%20for%20code%20review%20-%20CodeRabbit&text=I%20just%20used%20CodeRabbit%20for%20my%20code%20review%2C%20and%20it%27s%20fantastic%21%20It%27s%20free%20for%20OSS%20and%20offers%20a%20free%20trial%20for%20proprietary%20code.%20Check%20it%20out%3A%20https%3A//coderabbit.ai)\n- [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcoderabbit.ai&mini=true&title=Great%20tool%20for%20code%20review%20-%20CodeRabbit&summary=I%20just%20used%20CodeRabbit%20for%20my%20code%20review%2C%20and%20it%27s%20fantastic%21%20It